  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "F&B STORE MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u><br /><br /><strong>Operations Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Oversee, lead, and ensure smooth daily operations across all cafés and kiosks.</p></li><li><p>Implement and maintain operational standards and workflow efficiency.</p></li><li><p>Ensure full compliance with hygiene, safety, and regulatory requirements.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Staff Leadership & Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Supervise, mentor, and lead staff to deliver high-quality service.</p></li><li><p>Conduct staff training, coaching, and performance evaluations.</p></li><li><p>Manage staff records, including attendance, performance, and HR documentation.</p></li><li><p>Plan and prepare staff rosters; manage monthly timesheets.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Customer Relations</strong></p><ul><li><p>Build and maintain positive, professional relationships with customers.</p></li><li><p>Handle customer feedback and ensure service excellence.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Sales & Financial Management</strong></p><ul><li><p>Lead the team to achieve sales goals and drive revenue growth.</p></li><li><p>Monitor financial performance, control costs, and support budget management.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Administrative Duties</strong></p><ul><li>Manage documentation, reporting, and other store administrative tasks.</li></ul><ul><li><p>Undertake additional duties as assigned by management.</p></li></ul><ul><li>All other duties assigned by OM/Management</li></ul><p><strong></strong><br /><strong>Requirement</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum of 10 years of working experience in the Food & Beverage (F&B) sector.</li></ul><p><ul><li>Ability to commit to extended working hours as required by operational needs.</li></ul></p>",
